Under Crowd 2.0.4 using the SOAP API (via SecurityServerClient), when groups are queried using the searchGroups() method, all returned groups do not have the directoryID, description or the active flag set correctly.

e.g.
{code:xml}
com.atlassian.crowd.integration.soap.SOAPGroup@10901ce[ID=-1,name=confluence-administrators,directoryID=0,active=false,conception=<null>,lastModified=<null>,attributes=<null>,members={daniel}]
{code}

However, looking up a group directly using the findGroupByName() method returns the correct "active=true" result.

e.g.
{code:xml}
com.atlassian.crowd.integration.soap.SOAPGroup@4983d8[ID=-1,name=confluence-administrators,directoryID=327681,active=true,conception=<null>,lastModified=<null>,attributes={},members={daniel}]
{code}

We should check if other SOAP methods are affected by this type of bug.

First identified [here|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CWD-224?focusedCommentId=200870&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels%3Acomment-tabpanel#action_200870].

Currently, we show the number of users and the user_name of users that were not imported.

In addition to this, add the reasons why the import failed. For instance the lack of email information that is currently alerted in the log file only:
{noformat}
ERROR [crowd.model.principal.UserDAOHibernate]  Could not add user <rbattaglin>: user argument cannot have a null emailAddress
{noformat}

